# Cinderella

# There once was {a/an} {adjective} young girl named Cinderella who lived with her {adjective} stepmotherand two {adjective} stepsisters. She waited on them hand and {part of the body}, but they treated her like {a/an} {noun}. Cinderella heard about a ball the prince was throwing, but she didn't have {a/an} {adjective} gown to wear. Then, out of the clear, blue {noun}, her fairy {noun}-mother appeared and waved her magic {noun}. Cinderella's ragged clothes turned into a beautiful {noun}, and her worn work shoes became a pair of glass {plural noun}. Cinderella went to the ball and danced with Prince {Male name}, who fell madly in love with her. But at the stroke of midnight she had to flee, losing one of her glass {plural noun(same)}. The prince travelled throughout the kingdom, trying to find the matching {plural noun(same)}. He visited the {noun (place)} of every young girl until he found Cinderella, who had the other half of the {plural noun (same)}. Prince {Male name (same)} and Cinderella soon were married and lived {adverb} ever after!  


